# batch-pr-rebase-workflow — Version History

## v2.10.0 (2026-04-28)

**Changed by:** Mnemosyne 38-PR rebase session — CI fix rollout and conflict resolution patterns
**Verification:** verified-ci

### What changed
- Added trigger #25 (renumbered from old #25 in description): new CI job blocking all open PRs
  due to pre-existing violations (markdownlint/pixi-check on .claude/plugins/)
- Added trigger #26: two PRs independently amend same skill to same version with different
  content — treat as additive conflict, merge both sets of learnings, close redundant PR
- Added trigger #27: stale CI results requiring push to trigger fresh run
- Added 3 new "When to Use" bullets for all 3 patterns
- Added 3 new Failed Attempts rows:
  - Rebasing skill PRs when new CI job has pre-existing violations
  - Using git rebase --skip for superseded skill amendments without pushing
  - Auto-merge --rebase when repo only allows squash
- Added Quick Reference commands for all 3 patterns:
  - Check repo merge settings before auto-merge
  - Fix new CI job on main first, then rebase all PRs
  - Resolve two PRs with same version/different content via merge + close redundant

### Why
During the bulk rebase of 38 Mnemosyne skill PRs:
1. After PR #1441 landed markdownlint/pixi-check jobs, 11 skill PRs immediately failed CI due to
   pre-existing violations in .claude/plugins/ (not the PRs themselves). Pattern: fix root cause
   on main first, then rebase PRs.
2. PRs 1438 and 1440 both proposed v2.9.0 of batch-pr-rebase-workflow.md with different content.
   Neither could rebase cleanly. Resolved by merging both sets of learnings into one PR, closing
   the other as superseded.
3. PRs 1406 and 1432 both had v1.9.0 content superseded by v1.10.0 on main. Running
   git rebase --skip locally without pushing left the remote in a stale state.
4. gh pr merge --auto --rebase failed for all PRs — repo only allows squash merges.
   Should check merge settings before batch auto-merge.

